u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2180\" height=\"1458\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Obsidian Canvas\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/obsidian-tips-and-tricks-11.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\u003cp\u003e Obsidian supports an infinite canvas where you can use cards, different shapes, arrows, and more to freely brainstorm ideas, thoughts, and otherwise. You don’t need another whiteboard tool to get the job done, you can use the same right within your Obsidian vault.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003ch3 id=\"graph-view\"\u003e Graph view \u003c/h3\u003e\n\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=825\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=800\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=500\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"2162\" height=\"1432\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Obsidian global graph view\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/07/how-to-use-obsidian-graph-view-5.jpg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003e Both iA Writer and Obsidian support backlinks to connect your related notes and files. However, Obsidian is a step ahead, and you can check the relationship between such notes via a dedicated graph view.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"cloud-sync\"\u003e Cloud sync \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBoth iA Writer and Obsidian are quite flexible here. When you create a new vault in Obsidian, you can pick any location on your device to save your folders and notes. For example, it can be in OneDrive, Dropbox, Google Drive, or a local folder. iA Writer, by default, uses iCloud to sync your files and folders. However, you can always use another cloud storage of your choice to get the job done.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\u003cdiv data-include-community-rating=\"false\" id=\"d4e3-48ee-9e69ce03fac4\" data-nosnippet=\"\"\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/should-you-use-google-drive-onedrive-dropbox-or-nextcloud/\"\u003e\u003cdiv data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg\" data-modal-id=\"single-image-modal\" data-modal-container-id=\"single-image-modal-container\" data-img-caption=\"\u0026#34;\u0026#34;\"\u003e\u003cfigure\u003e\u003cpicture\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 1024px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=422\u0026amp;h=268\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 768px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=310\u0026amp;h=220\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 481px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=720\u0026amp;h=400\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\u003cimg width=\"1918\" height=\"1081\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"Which cloud storage service is better\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg\" src=\"https://static1.xdaimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/wm/2024/06/top-cloud-storage-services.jpeg\"/\u003e \u003c/picture\u003e \u003c/figure\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/a\u003e\u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\u003ch5\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/should-you-use-google-drive-onedrive-dropbox-or-nextcloud/\" title=\"Should you use Google Drive, OneDrive, Dropbox, or Nextcloud?\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e Should you use Google Drive, OneDrive, Dropbox, or Nextcloud? \u003c/a\u003e \u003c/h5\u003e\u003cp\u003eAnalyzing top cloud storage solutions: A deep dive into Google Drive, OneDrive, Dropbox, and Nextcloud\u003c/p\u003e \u003c/div\u003e \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"pricing-structure\"\u003e Pricing structure \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere is where it gets interesting. All Obsidian core features are completely free to use. You have a couple of paid add-ons like Sync ($5 per month) and Publish ($10 per month) to unlock end-to-end encryption, the ability to publish your notes on the web, and more.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eiA Writer works on a one-time purchase model. You need to make the one-time payment on the specific platforms on which you want to access iA Writer. It is priced at $50 on Mac, $50 on iPhone and iPad, and $30 on Windows.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\u003ch2 id=\"distraction-free-writing-vs-the-power-of-connections\"\u003e Distraction-free writing vs. the power of connections \u003c/h2\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eWith built-in Markdown support and connections, both iA Writer and Obsidian have nailed the basics. However, their similarities end here. While iA Writer has a better writing environment with focus mode, syntax, and style check, Obsidian marches ahead with third-party plugins, themes, graphs, and a superior pricing structure with an ample free plan. Ultimately, the choice between iA Writer and Obsidian hinges on your individual writing style and objectives.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n\n\n\n\u003cp\u003eObsidian is more than just a writing tool, though. You can use it to \u003ca href=\"https://www.xda-developers.com/how-to-use-obsidian-to-create-a-personal-knowledge-management-system/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ecreate a Personal Knowledge Management system\u003c/a\u003e as well - check out our separate guide to learn more.\u003c/p\u003e\n\n \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
